body:
@RoosterDragon I've made a new push which pushes even further the pathfinder. According to my tests, not only I've achieved performance boosts of +80-90% over the old pathfinder, but the current pathfinder now can GUARANTEE that the shortest path is given (previously it wasn't guaranteed, given the treatment that was done on closed/seen nodes). To achieve this, I applied several tactics over the priorityqueue and a comparer with the CellLayer array for realtime comparisons.

Now, there is lot of room for caching results and even develop a hierarchical pathfinding solution which would dramatically boost the pathfinder performance.

I would wish, if you are so kind, to provide me with feedback of your profilings with this new version and your comments on the code.

@pchote here there are a couple of profiling sessions I made. Left side of the image is the upstream/bleed profiling, and right side this PR results. The test has been made in the initial shellmap until the second time the screen turns grey. The results are quite interesting:

![profiling pathfinder](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5826108/6188087/20497134-b38e-11e4-9d7d-76e43336b58d.png)

Next step should be how to improve the validity of the cell (CanEnterCell), as it is the most time-consuming operation.

@MicroJOo could you do the following change to the code and test it again just to see if it may be a cache issue?

File \OpenRA.Mods.Common\Traits\World\Pathfinder\PathFinderInfo.cs, line 27.

Change: return new PathFinderCacheDecorator(new PathFinder(init.World), new PathCacheStorage(init.World));

To: return new PathFinder(init.World);

Thank you.
